  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We're now--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The family split.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The family split the affidavits.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father was hidden up in the mountains.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there is the infamous day arrives of Kristallnacht, November the 10th.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The building that we lived in, as I mentioned to you, was like a condominium.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One of the owners of the building, of his segment, was also the consul general of Guatemala.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he had the Office of the Consulate within the property, and his mother also lived in one of the units.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so always we had the emblem of the Consulate of Guatemala with, you know, the insignia of the state of-- and a flag was always flying on our building.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I saw it next to the one that were in our district where we lived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the reason they called it Kristallnacht is because when the windows broke, the stained windows and the beautiful windows, the-- the sound of the glass was like all the crystal broke all around, and it was totally devastating.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was the day they also tried to round up every Jew they could find and lay a hand on, rounding them up into trucks.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I saw the trucks because we lived on a main thoroughfare.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So a lot of things that had happened I was able to watch from the window, and you could see the trucks going by there filled with people.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said, Mama, what is happening?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she said to me, you children get dressed in double clothing right now.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we put on heavy clothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My mother had a feeling they were going to come and pick us up any minute.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] didn't take long, about an hour later, was a terrible banging on the door.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
